					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Magician guide 1- 40</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">billy joe bob</a> | 
		            2/6/2003 9:59:16 AM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">The level suggestions overlap in some places, meaning that you might want to go somewhere to hunt a little earlier or later, it's just personal preference.  <BR>
This guide can be used by any class in general, however some mage strategies are given.<BR>
<BR>
1 - 3<BR>
Local noob garden<BR>
nuff said<BR>
3 - 5<BR>
you can either keep hunting in your noob area, or you can head to steamfont and hunt the kobold camps.  if you are a hybrid or caster, i suggest hunting in noob garden till you get new spells then going to kobold camps<BR>
either that or partner with someone<BR>
5-6<BR>
you can stay at the kobold camps until 6, but the exp slows down.  head to orc hill or blackburrow if you're near qeynos.  i've also heard that misty thicket is good until about 12, but i've never hunted there.<BR>
6 - 8<BR>
solo or partner with someone and hunt low level centurions around the CB entrance<BR>
at 7 you can go to the orc camps in EC, but in my opinion thats a bit early, however do what you want.<BR>
8 - 12<BR>
group in CB or go to orc camps in EC<BR>
again blackburrow may serve you well at these levels, but i dont know much about blackburrow<BR>
11 - 13<BR>
go to derv camps in WC<BR>
if you're a pure caster i suggest waiting until your new spells at 12, as your level 8 ones wont work well against dervs.<BR>
if you're a hybrid, you should do fine<BR>
13 - 16<BR>
Get in a TR group in CB<BR>
16 - 17<BR>
i found that soloing legos is pretty decent exp in CB, <BR>
16 - 24 <BR>
head to PC and get in a bandit group<BR>
loot isn't too good but exp is AWESOME<BR>
these levels will fly by<BR>
24 - 32<BR>
HK in a GR group is pretty good exp, but spawns are slow<BR>
at 26 you might want to leave GR and go to RR or WR and group, but i stayed in GR until 27<BR>
Once you hit 31 or 32, if you dont mind the faction hit, take out HK guards.  pretty good exp and awesome loot.  also, the gnoll spawns by splitpaw in skarana are excellent exp, 4 spots, but often most are camped.  when camping the gnolls, as a mage, i nuked the gnoll to pull, set pet on it, ran around in circles with pet beating on it (sow is helpful), then when it aggroed on pet, nuked again until it aggroed, ran around in circles, repeat, repeat until dead<BR>
otherwise you can stay in RR or WR or you can head over to the overthere and group in an SF ramp group or ledge group at 30 plus or minus a couple levels.<BR>
i suggest staying at hk and taking guards/goblins in wr or rr till 34, then going to OT or staying with guards<BR>
goblin exp slows down around 34, so if you stay at HK, get guards<BR>
you can stay with HK guards till 37 or so, then exp slows down as well<BR>
34 - 37<BR>
Guard colin and Valon in WC are good exp, but horrible loot<BR>
wait until a spider or bear or something pulls one off to the side, then get the one still left at his post<BR>
37-40<BR>
Watchman halv in SF is good exp until 39, then you get a little less than half a blue every kill and spawns are 6 min each.<BR>
37 - 39<BR>
The troll tower in Rathe Mountains with Guard Gruilkin and Guard Shiznak are good exp<BR>
Gruilkin is a shammy so you have to watch out for poison, nukes etc<BR>
Shiznak is an sk so he has same sort of spells<BR>
both have pets<BR>
would suggest you only take them if you have fear or similar<BR>
they are each 6 min spawns, but if you break spawn then you get a spawn more often, depending on the time in between when you break the spawn.<BR>
Signus Boran in BB is good exp, about 3/4 a blue per kill, but 12.5 min spawn time (ugh)<BR>
<BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
